  "It proves that all trees grow at exactly the same rate": "",
  "Dendrochronology uses overlapping ring patterns from living trees, dead stumps, and preserved wood to build continuous chronologies extending up to approximately 12,000 years into the past, providing exact calendar-year dates.": "",
